uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.utils.parser

Class MZTabDataLineParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.utils.parser.MZTabLineParser
      • uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.utils.parser.MZTabDataLineParser
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PEPLineParser, PRTLineParser, PSMLineParser, SMLLineParser

    public abstract class MZTabDataLineParser
extends MZTabLineParser
    A couple of common method used to parse a data line into MZTabRecord structure. There are two step in data line parser process: step 1: data validate, these methods name start with "checkXXX()" focus on this. step 2: after validate, we fill the cell data into MZTabRecord, and use "loadXXX()" to generate the concrete record. NOTICE: MZTabColumnFactory maintain a couple of MZTabColumn which have internal logical position and order. In physical mzTab file, we allow user not obey this logical position organized way, and provide their date with own order. In order to distinguish them, we use physical position (a positive integer) to record the column location in mzTab file. And use PositionMapping structure the maintain the mapping between them.
    See Also:
    PRTLineParser, PEPLineParser, PSMLineParser, User: Qingwei Date: 14/02/13

        Parameters:
        column - SHOULD NOT set null
        calc_mass_to_charge - SHOULD NOT be empty.
